ternetlexikographischer Formate verändern unser traditionelles Bild vom Lexikon in erheblichem Maße. Der vorliegende Band orientiert sich an lexikalischen Phänomenen, deren Untersuchung diese Entwicklung prägt, und wirft Schlaglichter auf die gegenwärtige lexikologische Theorie und Praxis.  aOur traditional understanding of the lexicon has been changed by recent attention to the demarcation between grammar and the lexicon, increased attention to the phenomena of variance, the observation of quantitative divisions between lexical phenomena in large text corpora, and the development of Internet lexicographic formats. The volume explores the phenomena shaping these changes in order to describe current lexicological theory and practice.  afunded by Leibniz-Institut für Deutsche Sprache  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Feb 2021) 0aGerman languagexLexicology. 0aGerman languagexVocabulary. 4aLexikographie. 4aLexikologie. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh  aLexicology.  alexicography.1 aPlewnia, Albrecht, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWitt, Andreas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKellermeier-Rehbein, Birte, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBusse, Dietrich, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDobrovol'skij, Dmitrij, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEngelberg, Stefan, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aKämper, Heidrun, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFischer, Klaus, econtributor.4ctb4ht